    ### Bootstrapping the Application

    This is the Node file we will execute to serve up our web application. We load our app's configuration from an external file containing the HTTP port we want to run on and the MongoDB database connection string we need to store data using Mongoose.

    We also define four routes to be handled by our web application. Three of the routes are [webhooks](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Webhook) that will be requested by Twilio when your Twilio survey number receives an incoming call or text, or when the results of a transcription job are ready. The fourth route will be used by our reporting UI to get the results of the survey from the database.

    Now that our application is all set up, let's look at the high level steps necessary to implement a voice interview via Twilio and TwiML.